33namespace {
34constexpr TimeDelta kStreamTimeOut = TimeDelta::Seconds(2);
35
36// Used with field trial "WebRTC-Bwe-NewInterArrivalDelta/Enabled/
37constexpr TimeDelta kSendTimeGroupLength = TimeDelta::Millis(5);
38
39// Used unless field trial "WebRTC-Bwe-NewInterArrivalDelta/Enabled/"
40constexpr int kTimestampGroupLengthMs = 5;
41constexpr int kAbsSendTimeFraction = 18;
42constexpr int kAbsSendTimeInterArrivalUpshift = 8;
43constexpr int kInterArrivalShift =
44 kAbsSendTimeFraction + kAbsSendTimeInterArrivalUpshift;
45constexpr int kTimestampGroupTicks =
46 (kTimestampGroupLengthMs << kInterArrivalShift) / 1000;
47constexpr double kTimestampToMs =
48 1000.0 / static_cast<double>(1 << kInterArrivalShift);
49
50// This ssrc is used to fulfill the current API but will be removed
51// after the API has been changed.
52constexpr uint32_t kFixedSsrc = 0;
53} // namespace

71DelayBasedBwe::Result::Result()
72 : updated(false),
73 probe(false),
74 target_bitrate(DataRate::Zero()),
75 recovered_from_overuse(false),
76 backoff_in_alr(false) {}

78DelayBasedBwe::DelayBasedBwe(const WebRtcKeyValueConfig* key_value_config,
79 RtcEventLog* event_log,
80 NetworkStatePredictor* network_state_predictor)
81 : event_log_(event_log),
82 key_value_config_(key_value_config),
83 separate_audio_(key_value_config),
84 audio_packets_since_last_video_(0),
85 last_video_packet_recv_time_(Timestamp::MinusInfinity()),
86 network_state_predictor_(network_state_predictor),
87 video_delay_detector_(
88 new TrendlineEstimator(key_value_config_, network_state_predictor_)),
89 audio_delay_detector_(
90 new TrendlineEstimator(key_value_config_, network_state_predictor_)),
91 active_delay_detector_(video_delay_detector_.get()),
92 last_seen_packet_(Timestamp::MinusInfinity()),
93 uma_recorded_(false),
94 rate_control_(key_value_config, /*send_side=*/true),
95 prev_bitrate_(DataRate::Zero()),
96 has_once_detected_overuse_(false),
97 prev_state_(BandwidthUsage::kBwNormal),
98 use_new_inter_arrival_delta_(absl::StartsWith(
99 key_value_config->Lookup("WebRTC-Bwe-NewInterArrivalDelta"),
100 "Enabled")),
101 alr_limited_backoff_enabled_(absl::StartsWith(
102 key_value_config->Lookup("WebRTC-Bwe-AlrLimitedBackoff"),
103 "Enabled")) {
104 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO)
105 << "Initialized DelayBasedBwe with separate audio overuse detection"
106 << separate_audio_.Parser()->Encode() << " and alr limited backoff "
107 << (alr_limited_backoff_enabled_ ? "enabled" : "disabled");
108}

110DelayBasedBwe::~DelayBasedBwe() {}

112DelayBasedBwe::Result DelayBasedBwe::IncomingPacketFeedbackVector(
113 const TransportPacketsFeedback& msg,
114 absl::optional<DataRate> acked_bitrate,
115 absl::optional<DataRate> probe_bitrate,
116 absl::optional<NetworkStateEstimate> network_estimate,
117 bool in_alr) {
118 RTC_DCHECK_RUNS_SERIALIZED(&network_race_);
119
120 auto packet_feedback_vector = msg.SortedByReceiveTime();
121 // TODO(holmer): An empty feedback vector here likely means that
122 // all acks were too late and that the send time history had
123 // timed out. We should reduce the rate when this occurs.
124 if (packet_feedback_vector.empty()) {
125 RTC_LOG(LS_WARNING) << "Very late feedback received.";
126 return DelayBasedBwe::Result();
127 }
128
129 if (!uma_recorded_) {
130 RTC_HISTOGRAM_ENUMERATION(kBweTypeHistogram,
131 BweNames::kSendSideTransportSeqNum,
132 BweNames::kBweNamesMax);
133 uma_recorded_ = true;
134 }
135 bool delayed_feedback = true;
136 bool recovered_from_overuse = false;
137 BandwidthUsage prev_detector_state = active_delay_detector_->State();
138 for (const auto& packet_feedback : packet_feedback_vector) {
139 delayed_feedback = false;
140 IncomingPacketFeedback(packet_feedback, msg.feedback_time);
141 if (prev_detector_state == BandwidthUsage::kBwUnderusing &&
142 active_delay_detector_->State() == BandwidthUsage::kBwNormal) {
143 recovered_from_overuse = true;
144 }
145 prev_detector_state = active_delay_detector_->State();
146 }
147
148 if (delayed_feedback) {
149 // TODO(bugs.webrtc.org/10125): Design a better mechanism to safe-guard
150 // against building very large network queues.
151 return Result();
152 }
153 rate_control_.SetInApplicationLimitedRegion(in_alr);
154 rate_control_.SetNetworkStateEstimate(network_estimate);
155 return MaybeUpdateEstimate(acked_bitrate, probe_bitrate,
156 std::move(network_estimate),
157 recovered_from_overuse, in_alr, msg.feedback_time);
158}
159
160void DelayBasedBwe::IncomingPacketFeedback(const PacketResult& packet_feedback,
161 Timestamp at_time) {
162 // Reset if the stream has timed out.
163 if (last_seen_packet_.IsInfinite() ||
164 at_time - last_seen_packet_ > kStreamTimeOut) {
165 if (use_new_inter_arrival_delta_) {
166 video_inter_arrival_delta_ =
167 std::make_unique<InterArrivalDelta>(kSendTimeGroupLength);
168 audio_inter_arrival_delta_ =
169 std::make_unique<InterArrivalDelta>(kSendTimeGroupLength);
170 } else {
171 video_inter_arrival_ = std::make_unique<InterArrival>(
172 kTimestampGroupTicks, kTimestampToMs, true);
173 audio_inter_arrival_ = std::make_unique<InterArrival>(
174 kTimestampGroupTicks, kTimestampToMs, true);
175 }
176 video_delay_detector_.reset(
177 new TrendlineEstimator(key_value_config_, network_state_predictor_));
178 audio_delay_detector_.reset(
179 new TrendlineEstimator(key_value_config_, network_state_predictor_));
180 active_delay_detector_ = video_delay_detector_.get();
181 }
182 last_seen_packet_ = at_time;
183
184 // As an alternative to ignoring small packets, we can separate audio and
185 // video packets for overuse detection.
186 DelayIncreaseDetectorInterface* delay_detector_for_packet =
187 video_delay_detector_.get();
188 if (separate_audio_.enabled) {
189 if (packet_feedback.sent_packet.audio) {
190 delay_detector_for_packet = audio_delay_detector_.get();
191 audio_packets_since_last_video_++;
192 if (audio_packets_since_last_video_ > separate_audio_.packet_threshold &&
193 packet_feedback.receive_time - last_video_packet_recv_time_ >
194 separate_audio_.time_threshold) {
195 active_delay_detector_ = audio_delay_detector_.get();
196 }
197 } else {
198 audio_packets_since_last_video_ = 0;
199 last_video_packet_recv_time_ =
200 std::max(last_video_packet_recv_time_, packet_feedback.receive_time);
201 active_delay_detector_ = video_delay_detector_.get();
202 }
203 }
204 DataSize packet_size = packet_feedback.sent_packet.size;
205
206 if (use_new_inter_arrival_delta_) {
207 TimeDelta send_delta = TimeDelta::Zero();
208 TimeDelta recv_delta = TimeDelta::Zero();
209 int size_delta = 0;
210
211 InterArrivalDelta* inter_arrival_for_packet =
212 (separate_audio_.enabled && packet_feedback.sent_packet.audio)
213 ? video_inter_arrival_delta_.get()
214 : audio_inter_arrival_delta_.get();
215 bool calculated_deltas = inter_arrival_for_packet->ComputeDeltas(
216 packet_feedback.sent_packet.send_time, packet_feedback.receive_time,
217 at_time, packet_size.bytes(), &send_delta, &recv_delta, &size_delta);
218
219 delay_detector_for_packet->Update(
220 recv_delta.ms(), send_delta.ms(),
221 packet_feedback.sent_packet.send_time.ms(),
222 packet_feedback.receive_time.ms(), packet_size.bytes(),
223 calculated_deltas);
224 } else {
225 InterArrival* inter_arrival_for_packet =
226 (separate_audio_.enabled && packet_feedback.sent_packet.audio)
227 ? video_inter_arrival_.get()
228 : audio_inter_arrival_.get();
229
230 uint32_t send_time_24bits =
231 static_cast<uint32_t>(
232 ((static_cast<uint64_t>(packet_feedback.sent_packet.send_time.ms())
233 << kAbsSendTimeFraction) +
234 500) /
235 1000) &
236 0x00FFFFFF;
237 // Shift up send time to use the full 32 bits that inter_arrival works with,
238 // so wrapping works properly.
239 uint32_t timestamp = send_time_24bits << kAbsSendTimeInterArrivalUpshift;
240
241 uint32_t timestamp_delta = 0;
242 int64_t recv_delta_ms = 0;
243 int size_delta = 0;
244
245 bool calculated_deltas = inter_arrival_for_packet->ComputeDeltas(
246 timestamp, packet_feedback.receive_time.ms(), at_time.ms(),
247 packet_size.bytes(), &timestamp_delta, &recv_delta_ms, &size_delta);
248 double send_delta_ms =
249 (1000.0 * timestamp_delta) / (1 << kInterArrivalShift);
250
251 delay_detector_for_packet->Update(
252 recv_delta_ms, send_delta_ms,
253 packet_feedback.sent_packet.send_time.ms(),
254 packet_feedback.receive_time.ms(), packet_size.bytes(),
255 calculated_deltas);
256 }
257}

259DataRate DelayBasedBwe::TriggerOveruse(Timestamp at_time,
260 absl::optional<DataRate> link_capacity) {
261 RateControlInput input(BandwidthUsage::kBwOverusing, link_capacity);
262 return rate_control_.Update(&input, at_time);
263}
264
265DelayBasedBwe::Result DelayBasedBwe::MaybeUpdateEstimate(
266 absl::optional<DataRate> acked_bitrate,
267 absl::optional<DataRate> probe_bitrate,
268 absl::optional<NetworkStateEstimate> state_estimate,
269 bool recovered_from_overuse,
270 bool in_alr,
271 Timestamp at_time) {
272 Result result;
273
274 // Currently overusing the bandwidth.
275 if (active_delay_detector_->State() == BandwidthUsage::kBwOverusing) {
276 if (has_once_detected_overuse_ && in_alr && alr_limited_backoff_enabled_) {
277 if (rate_control_.TimeToReduceFurther(at_time, prev_bitrate_)) {
278 result.updated =
279 UpdateEstimate(at_time, prev_bitrate_, &result.target_bitrate);
280 result.backoff_in_alr = true;
281 }
282 } else if (acked_bitrate &&
283 rate_control_.TimeToReduceFurther(at_time, *acked_bitrate)) {
284 result.updated =
285 UpdateEstimate(at_time, acked_bitrate, &result.target_bitrate);
286 } else if (!acked_bitrate && rate_control_.ValidEstimate() &&
287 rate_control_.InitialTimeToReduceFurther(at_time)) {
288 // Overusing before we have a measured acknowledged bitrate. Reduce send
289 // rate by 50% every 200 ms.
290 // TODO(tschumim): Improve this and/or the acknowledged bitrate estimator
291 // so that we (almost) always have a bitrate estimate.
292 rate_control_.SetEstimate(rate_control_.LatestEstimate() / 2, at_time);
293 result.updated = true;
294 result.probe = false;
295 result.target_bitrate = rate_control_.LatestEstimate();
296 }
297 has_once_detected_overuse_ = true;
298 } else {
299 if (probe_bitrate) {
300 result.probe = true;
301 result.updated = true;
302 result.target_bitrate = *probe_bitrate;
303 rate_control_.SetEstimate(*probe_bitrate, at_time);
304 } else {
305 result.updated =
306 UpdateEstimate(at_time, acked_bitrate, &result.target_bitrate);
307 result.recovered_from_overuse = recovered_from_overuse;
308 }
309 }
310 BandwidthUsage detector_state = active_delay_detector_->State();
311 if ((result.updated && prev_bitrate_ != result.target_bitrate) ||
312 detector_state != prev_state_) {
313 DataRate bitrate = result.updated ? result.target_bitrate : prev_bitrate_;
314
315 BWE_TEST_LOGGING_PLOT(1, "target_bitrate_bps", at_time.ms(), bitrate.bps());
316
317 if (event_log_) {
318 event_log_->Log(std::make_unique<RtcEventBweUpdateDelayBased>(
319 bitrate.bps(), detector_state));
320 }
321
322 prev_bitrate_ = bitrate;
323 prev_state_ = detector_state;
324 }
325 return result;
326}
327
328bool DelayBasedBwe::UpdateEstimate(Timestamp at_time,
329 absl::optional<DataRate> acked_bitrate,
330 DataRate* target_rate) {
331 const RateControlInput input(active_delay_detector_->State(), acked_bitrate);
332 *target_rate = rate_control_.Update(&input, at_time);
333 return rate_control_.ValidEstimate();
334}
335
336void DelayBasedBwe::OnRttUpdate(TimeDelta avg_rtt) {
337 rate_control_.SetRtt(avg_rtt);
338}
339
340bool DelayBasedBwe::LatestEstimate(std::vector<uint32_t>* ssrcs,
341 DataRate* bitrate) const {
342 // Currently accessed from both the process thread (see
343 // ModuleRtpRtcpImpl::Process()) and the configuration thread (see
344 // Call::GetStats()). Should in the future only be accessed from a single
345 // thread.
346 RTC_DCHECK(ssrcs);
347 RTC_DCHECK(bitrate);
348 if (!rate_control_.ValidEstimate())
349 return false;
350
351 *ssrcs = {kFixedSsrc};
352 *bitrate = rate_control_.LatestEstimate();
353 return true;
354}
355
356void DelayBasedBwe::SetStartBitrate(DataRate start_bitrate) {
357 RTC_LOG(LS_INFO) << "BWE Setting start bitrate to: "
358 << ToString(start_bitrate);
359 rate_control_.SetStartBitrate(start_bitrate);
360}
361
362void DelayBasedBwe::SetMinBitrate(DataRate min_bitrate) {
363 // Called from both the configuration thread and the network thread. Shouldn't
364 // be called from the network thread in the future.
365 rate_control_.SetMinBitrate(min_bitrate);
366}
